==English==
===Etymology===
"'''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TMI Too Much Information]'''," a humorous expression, sometimes known as [[Internet slang]], used in [[North America]] and the [[United Kingdom]] to inform a speaker that he/she is telling or revealing too much about himself/herself or a given topic to the level that the topic becomes gross.  The author of this phrase is unknown, but is a suspected and widely supported idea that it began in the Northwest, United States.

===Noun===
'''TMI'''
# Information of a personal nature that causes the receipient to be grossed out.
#: ''He began to talk about spitting his teeth out after loosing them as a child.  I told him, 'TMI!'''